rict final display format.\\n\\n4.  **Refining Testbench Logic:**\\n    *   The original testbench uses `assign tb_match = ( { q_ref } === ( { q_ref } ^ { q_dut } ^ { q_ref } ) );`. This assignment seems designed to test if `q_dut` equals `q_ref`. If $q_{ref} = q_{dut}$, then $q_{ref} \\text{ XOR } q_{dut} \\text{ XOR } q_{ref} = 0 \\text{ XOR } q_{ref} = q_{ref}$. The comparison becomes $q_{ref} === q_{ref}$, which is always true if the XOR logic holds. A simpler check for $q_{ref} == q_{dut}$ is more appropriate for a standard comparison, but I must maintain the original functionality. I will stick to the original assignment for `tb_match`.\\n    *   The original mismatch check: `if (!tb_match)` increments errors. \\n    *   The original queueing logic in the testbench is complex and uses `stats1.errors_q` which seems redundant or specific to the original implementation. I will implement the *new* required queueing structure based on the prompt\'s example, focusing on storing inputs and outputs to detect mismatches using the queue.\\n\\n5.  **Final Display Requirement:**\\n    *   The final display must be: `"    \n        \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n   